## 5. TABELA DE VENDAS

`ad_id` recebe o valor bruto de `utm_content` que chega no webhook do checkout.
O trigger `match_sale_to_ad` resolve automaticamente os campos `matched_*`
subindo a hierarquia: anúncio → conjunto → campanha.

```sql
CREATE TABLE public.sales (
  id                  UUID DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() PRIMARY KEY,
  checkout_platform   TEXT NOT NULL
                        CHECK (checkout_platform IN ('hotmart', 'kiwify', 'kirvano')),
  transaction_id      TEXT NOT NULL,
  product_name        TEXT,
  product_id          TEXT,
  buyer_name          TEXT,
  buyer_email         TEXT,
  amount              NUMERIC(12,2) NOT NULL,
  currency            TEXT DEFAULT 'BRL',
  status              TEXT DEFAULT 'approved'
                        CHECK (status IN ('approved','pending','refunded','cancelled','chargeback')),
  payment_method      TEXT,

  -- Campos UTM recebidos do checkout
  utm_source          TEXT,
  utm_medium          TEXT,
  utm_campaign        TEXT,
  utm_content         TEXT,
  utm_term            TEXT,

  -- Chave de cruzamento central (= facebook_ad_id vindo de utm_content)
  ad_id               TEXT,

  -- Referências resolvidas automaticamente pelo trigger
  matched_ad_id       UUID REFERENCES public.ads(id),
  matched_ad_set_id   UUID REFERENCES public.ad_sets(id),
  matched_campaign_id UUID REFERENCES public.campaigns(id),

  is_organic          BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  sale_date           TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  raw_webhook_data    JSONB,
  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_sales_ad_id            ON public.sales(ad_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_sales_matched_ad       ON public.sales(matched_ad_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_sales_matched_adset    ON public.sales(matched_ad_set_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_sales_matched_campaign ON public.sales(matched_campaign_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_sales_sale_date        ON public.sales(sale_date);
```

